File: A health department official collects samples from a man during a door-to-door COVID-19 testing drive. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa's COVID-19 infections have increased by 124 since Saturday. This brings to 3,158 the number of people who've tested positive for the coronavirus. Another two people have died, one in the Western Cape and one in KwaZulu-Natal. This brings the total deaths to 54. Health Dept Media Release by eNCA.com on Scribd 